Maintainer: Debian Fonts Task Force <pkg-fonts-devel@lists.alioth.debian.org>
Installed-Size: 25074
Section: contrib/fonts
Priority: optional
Multi-Arch: foreign
Homepage: https://www.ibm.com/plex/
Description: extensive typeface family designed by IBM
 Plex is an extensive font family developed by IBM. It comes in four
 subfamilies (Sans, Mono, Serif and Condensed), two styles (roman and
 italic) and 8 weights (Thin, Extralight, Light, Regular, Text, Medium,
 Semibold, Bold).
 .
 Plex supports mosts of the Latin languages (including Vietnamese),
 monotonic Greek, Hebrew (including cantillation marks), Thai, and the
 Cyrillic writing system, for a total of over 100 languages. Support
 for Arabic, Devanagari, Chinese, Japanese, Korean, Bengali and Tamil
 is planned. There is also support for common mathematical and currency
 symbols as well as ligatures and stylistic alternates.
 .
 This package contains the PostScript (CFF) flavored OpenType fonts and
 the WOFF/WOFF2 web fonts.
